			<h2 id="what-is">
				<span class="hash">#</span>What Swiggy Instamart Onboarding Really
				Means
			</h2>
			<p>
				The most important thing to understand about Instamart is that <strong>you
					are a supplier to Swiggy, not a seller on a marketplace</strong>. On
				platforms like Amazon or Flipkart, you list and price your own
				products. On Instamart, Swiggy purchases your stock into its dark
				stores and controls the retail experience &mdash; pricing,
				promotion, and placement.
			</p>
			<p>This B2B supply framing shapes everything: the commercial
				negotiation with a Category Manager, the strict per-SKU catalogue
				approval (NPI), the inventory you push into dark stores, and how
				performance is measured. It is closer to getting listed by a modern
				retailer than opening a marketplace storefront &mdash; and it
				rewards brands that come in prepared and well-advised.</p>

			<h2 id="supply-model">
				<span class="hash">#</span>How the Instamart Supply Model Works
			</h2>
			<p>Because Instamart buys and resells your stock, the flow of
				goods and money is different from a marketplace. Understanding this
				flow makes every later decision &mdash; pricing, inventory,
				promotions &mdash; far clearer:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>You supply.</strong> After onboarding, you dispatch
					inventory to Swiggy&rsquo;s warehouse or dark stores against a
					purchase order raised by Instamart.</li>
				<li><strong>Instamart stocks and sells.</strong> Your products
					are distributed across the dark-store network in your approved
					cities and sold to customers through the app.</li>
				<li><strong>Swiggy controls the storefront.</strong> Pricing,
					placement, and promotions on the customer side are managed by
					Instamart, informed by the commercial terms agreed during
					onboarding.</li>
				<li><strong>You are paid on a cycle.</strong> Settlements are
					made on Instamart&rsquo;s payment cycle for the stock it has taken
					and sold, after applicable deductions.</li>
				<li><strong>Performance drives expansion.</strong> Strong
					sell-through earns you more cities, more SKUs, and larger purchase
					orders over time.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>The practical implication is simple: your job is to be an
				excellent, reliable supplier with a compelling, compliant catalogue
				&mdash; and IARDO&rsquo;s job is to get you set up to be exactly
				that, quickly and correctly, so you spend your energy on product and
				supply rather than paperwork and process.</p>

			<h2 id="why-sell">
				<span class="hash">#</span>Why Sell on Swiggy Instamart?
			</h2>
			<p>Quick commerce is one of the fastest-growing retail channels
				in India, and Instamart sits at the front of it. For brands, that
				combination of speed, scale, and repeat buying behaviour is hard to
				match anywhere else &mdash; and getting in early, before your
				category is crowded, is a genuine advantage. Here is why brands
				prioritise it:</p>
			<div class="perks">
				<div class="card">
					<h4>
						<span class="v">&#10003;</span>Massive Quick-Commerce Reach
					</h4>
					<p>Instamart taps into Swiggy&rsquo;s enormous existing user
						base across major metros and fast-growing cities, driving high
						daily order volumes.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<h4>
						<span class="v">&#10003;</span>High-Intent, Repeat Buyers
					</h4>
					<p>Customers order everyday essentials on convenience and
						reorder constantly &mdash; ideal for FMCG, personal care, and food
						brands.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<h4>
						<span class="v">&#10003;</span>Platform-Handled Logistics
					</h4>
					<p>Swiggy manages distribution from dark stores and last-mile
						delivery &mdash; you focus on supply and catalogue.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<h4>
						<span class="v">&#10003;</span>Demand-Led Reordering
					</h4>
					<p>Once you prove velocity, Swiggy reorders based on real
						sell-through and expands you to more cities and SKUs.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 id="right-fit">
				<span class="hash">#</span>Is Swiggy Instamart Right for Your Brand?
			</h2>
			<p>Instamart rewards some brands more than others, and being
				honest about fit saves everyone time. The channel tends to work best
				for:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Everyday, frequently bought products</strong>
					&mdash; packaged food, beverages, personal care, household, and
					other essentials that customers reorder on convenience.</li>
				<li><strong>Compact, easy-to-deliver SKUs</strong> that suit
					the dark-store and minutes-delivery model.</li>
				<li><strong>Products with healthy margins</strong> that can
					absorb the full cost of selling and still leave room to grow.</li>
				<li><strong>Brands ready to supply reliably</strong> &mdash;
					consistent availability is the foundation of everything that
					follows.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>If your product fits this profile, Instamart can become one of
				your strongest channels. If it does not fit neatly, IARDO will tell
				you honestly and help you weigh whether Instamart, Blinkit, or
				another platform is the better first move &mdash; because a launch
				that suits your product is worth far more than a launch for its own
				sake.</p>

			<h2 id="pathways">
				<span class="hash">#</span>The Two Onboarding Pathways
			</h2>
			<p>There are two ways a brand gets onto Instamart, and knowing
				which applies to you saves weeks:</p>
			<div class="pick">
				<div class="opt">
					<h4>1. Direct Supplier Empanelment</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>You apply through the Swiggy Instamart partner portal</li>
						<li>Submit business, KYC, and catalogue details</li>
						<li>Best for new and growing brands proactively entering the
							channel</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="opt alt">
					<h4>2. Inbound Category Outreach</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Swiggy&rsquo;s category team reaches out to established
							brands</li>
						<li>More common for brands with existing retail traction</li>
						<li>Faster commercial conversations, but on Swiggy&rsquo;s
							timeline</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			<p>IARDO positions your brand for whichever pathway fits &mdash;
				preparing a clean application for direct empanelment, or a strong
				pitch that attracts category-team interest.</p>

			<h2 id="documents">
				<span class="hash">#</span>Documents Required for Swiggy Instamart
			</h2>
			<p>Getting your documents clean and consistent upfront is the
				single biggest factor in how fast you go live. A valid GSTIN is
				mandatory, and the business name must match across all records. For
				multi-city supply, each dark-store state must be added to your GST.</p>
			<p>Beyond the core paperwork, Instamart&rsquo;s supply model adds
				a few requirements that marketplace sellers often overlook &mdash;
				most notably GS1-registered barcodes for every SKU and, for food and
				grocery, an FSSAI licence with sufficient validity and details
				printed clearly on the pack. Getting these in order before you apply
				is what keeps the whole process moving; scrambling for them
				mid-review is what stalls it. IARDO audits your documentation
				against Instamart&rsquo;s exact checklist at the very start, so
				nothing surfaces late to reset the clock.</p>
