			<h2 id="vs-market">
				<span class="hash">#</span>Instamart vs a Marketplace: What Changes
				for Sellers
			</h2>
			<p>If your experience so far is with Amazon, Flipkart, or Meesho,
				it helps to name exactly what is different on Instamart, because
				those differences change how you plan:</p>
			<div class="tbl-wrap">
				<table>
					<thead>
						<tr>
							<th>Aspect</th>
							<th>Marketplace (e.g. Amazon)</th>
							<th>Swiggy Instamart</th>
						</tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td>Your role</td>
							<td>Seller listing to customers</td>
							<td>Supplier to Swiggy</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>Who sets price</td>
							<td>You</td>
							<td>Swiggy (per agreed terms)</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>Who holds stock</td>
							<td>You or the platform</td>
							<td>Swiggy&rsquo;s dark stores</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>Catalogue approval</td>
							<td>Largely self-serve</td>
							<td>Per-SKU NPI review</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>Delivery</td>
							<td>Standard, next-day+</td>
							<td>Minutes, hyperlocal</td>
