			<h2 id="faq">
				<span class="hash">#</span>Frequently Asked Questions
			</h2>
			<div class="faq">
				<details open>
					<summary>What are Swiggy Instamart onboarding services?</summary>
					<div class="ans">Swiggy Instamart onboarding services help
						brands become approved suppliers on Instamart &mdash; covering
						supplier registration and KYC, documentation, NPI catalogue
						creation, Category Manager coordination, inventory setup, and
						post-go-live support. IARDO manages this end-to-end.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Is selling on Swiggy Instamart the same as a
						marketplace?</summary>
					<div class="ans">No. Instamart runs on a B2B supply model
						&mdash; you are a supplier to Swiggy, not a seller on a
						marketplace. Swiggy purchases your stock into its dark stores and
						retails it to customers, which shapes the entire onboarding,
						pricing, and catalogue process.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>What is NPI in Swiggy Instamart onboarding?</summary>
					<div class="ans">NPI (New Product Introduction) is
						Instamart&rsquo;s process of individually reviewing and approving
						each SKU before it goes live &mdash; covering title format, image
						specs, GS1 barcodes, HSN codes, MRP matching, and FSSAI compliance
						on packaging.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>How long does Swiggy Instamart onboarding take?</summary>
					<div class="ans">For a well-prepared brand, typically around
						six to eight weeks from registration to going live; brands with
						incomplete documents or catalogues can take two to four months.
						IARDO handles the process to keep it on track.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>What documents are needed for Swiggy Instamart?</summary>
					<div class="ans">A GST-registered business, PAN, cancelled
						cheque, business registration, authorised signatory details, FSSAI
						for food, GS1 barcodes, and APOB GST for multi-state supply. IARDO
						prepares and verifies all documentation.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Is the onboarding fee refundable?</summary>
					<div class="ans">Yes. IARDO&rsquo;s Swiggy Instamart
						onboarding engagement is fully refundable if your account does not
						go live.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>How many SKUs should I launch with on Instamart?</summary>
					<div class="ans">A focused set of high-demand SKUs &mdash;
						often around five to ten to start &mdash; usually outperforms a
						large, scattered catalogue. You earn more SKUs and cities by
						proving velocity on a strong initial range, and IARDO helps you
						choose the right ones to launch with.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Can I start on Instamart in just one or two
						cities?</summary>
					<div class="ans">Yes, and it is often the smart approach.
						Most brands begin in one or two cities, prove sell-through, and
						then expand to more cities and dark stores as performance
